TY  - JOUR
AU  - Gropp, Reint
AU  - Vesala, Jukka
T1  - Deposit Insurance, Moral Hazard and Market Monitoring*
PY  - 2004
Y1  - 2004/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/8.4.571
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 8
IS  - 4
SP  - 571
EP  - 602
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - The paper analyses the relationship between deposit insurance, debt-holder monitoring, and risk taking. In a stylised banking model we show that deposit insurance may reduce moral hazard, if deposit insurance credibly leaves out non-deposit creditors. Testing the model using EU bank level data yields evidence consistent with the model, suggesting that explicit deposit insurance may serve as a commitment device to limit the safety net and permit monitoring by uninsured subordinated debt holders. We further find that credible limits to the safety net reduce risk taking of smaller banks with low charter values and sizeable subordinated debt shares only. However, we also find that the introduction of explicit deposit insurance tends to increase the share of insured deposits in banks' liabilities.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/8.4.571
ER  - 



